<item>
            <title>[CXF-7629] When registering a provider that implements MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter interfaces through a Feature CXF ignores the interfaces in the contract and registers them all</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7629</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when using&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
javax.ws.rs.core.Configurable#register(java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;, MessageBodyReader.class)

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to register a provider that implements both MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter, CXF ignores the specified contract and registers the provider for both MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter, instead of only for MessageBodyReader.class.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13135472">CXF-7629</key>
            <summary>When registering a provider that implements MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter interfaces through a Feature CXF ignores the interfaces in the contract and registers them all</summary>
